"Hey, why don't you come to my home in Hungary?"[l][r]
Yuri said that to me first. I tilted my head, curious.[r]
"Huh?" Water was still dripping from Yuri's hair.[l][r]
"It's a nice place. In Pest... the eastern outskirts of Budapest. It's rural enough, but just a short bike ride to the city. Can you ride a bike, Chi-chan?"[l][r]
"What's... with you all of a sudden?"[r]
"Why not? Even if it's sudden." [l][r]
Yuri replied with a silly grin. Her usual face, yet it somehow felt nostalgic.[l][r]
"I'm not in the mood." I tried to push her away with my words.[l][r]
"That's exactly why." Yuri persisted.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"Chi-chan, you said it. This world is too fulfilling. But try coming to my place. You can't even understand the language.[l] My family is kind, my mother is Japanese, and my father speaks Japanese too, but knowing you, you'd be shy initially, right?[l][r]
Do you still think you could say this world is too fulfilling in such a place?"[l][r]
Yuri said, smiling mischievously.[l][r]
Oh, you... you are truly kind.[l][r]
But I know. We've been together so long.[l][r]
When you're forcing a smile, the corners of your mouth rise just a bit too much...[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"...Sorry." [r]
"For what?"[l][r]
Kind Yuri. She cherishes everything about me. But that's not the kind of kindness I need.[l][r]
"I can't go to your house." I said, barely looking at her eyes.[l][r]
"Because... knowing you have family besides me... I can't bear it."[l][r]
"......"[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
I confessed, my voice choking, hiding nothing. My selfish reasons.[l][r]
...When did it start? Since when did I become such a helpless human being?[l][r]
"I only need you. I don't want you to see anyone else but me. So I can't go." I continued my nonsensical excuses.[l][r]
"You're right. I understand." [l][r]
Yuri answered with a voice devoid of any emotion.[l][r]
Her smile vanished from her face.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[bg  time="1500"  method="crossfade"  storage="black.png"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
Ah...[l][r]
Just for a moment. It felt like all the light had disappeared from the world.[l][r]
"Then I'll tell you what I want. So much that I'd give up everything else I love... I'll tell you." [r]
A voice echoed from the darkness.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"I want Chi-chan to be happy."[l][r]
That's wrong.[r]
Those words are wrong.[l][r]
I don't need that.[r]
Those words are inappropriate.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
I don't need to be happy. [l][r]
You don't need to be happy either. [l][r]
What I want is you, just you. [l][r]
Not your happiness.[l][r]
I don't need happiness. [l][r]
Happiness is a bothersome thing. [l][r]
In this troublesome world, how much misfortune must one endure to constantly attain such an uncertain and unstable thing as happiness?[l][r]
Can’t you imagine that?[l][r]
Can't you, who is such an idiot, imagine that?[l][r]
Jealousy, envy, dissatisfaction, anxiety, a sense of futility, a feeling of helplessness.[l][r]
Happy days that could be shattered anytime by anyone are just terrifying.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]

Yes, [r]
I'm scared, scared, terrified! [r]
I never want to lose you, never again... not you or myself.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

