I heard a bursting sound in my head.[l][r]

It was just my imagination, just a loud noise right next to my ear. And then came the delay of pain.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[bg  time="2000"  method="crossfade"  storage="tomosibi.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
My cheek was hot.[l][r]
I felt like the heat, pain, and sound ignited a small flame in the darkness. It illuminated a crying girl's face before me.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
Tears were streaming down her face. She was crying, eyes closed in frustration. And then,[l][r]

Her closed eyes,[r]
moved closer to me,[l][r]

her lips gently touched mine.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[playbgm  volume="100"  time="1000"  loop="false"  storage="m5_piano.ogg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"It's okay."[l][r]
Yuri whispered in my ear.[l][r]
"It's okay. Chi-chan, you're not wrong."[l][r]
It felt like a small, tiny sun was shining there.[l][r]

"But listen."[l][r]
The tiny sun, like a child's, brightly lit the darkness, bringing light and warmth to my ear, my cheek.[l][r]
"I won't give up on what I want. I'm greedy, you know? Always hungry." [r]
You know that, right? I'm always hungry."[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
A single raindrop fell onto my sunlit cheek.[l][r]
Yuri sniffled a bit.[l][r]

"That's why... I won't let go. No matter how sad, painful, troublesome, unhappy, or despairing it gets.[l][r]
Because I'm good at it. I’m good at getting along with despair."[l][r]

There was a chuckle.[l][r]
Maybe that chuckle wasn’t even hers.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
Warmth spread through me.[l][r]
From my shoulders, to my back, to the tips of my toes, that warmth and light reached everywhere.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[bg  time="1500"  method="crossfade"  storage="room5_asa.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
Morning had come.[l][r]
Rain-kissed light pouring through the curtains filled the messy room with a warm, bright glow.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"Let's go together. If you hate here and hate my home, anywhere is fine.[l][r]
Let's search again for our world. For our home." [l][r]
"A home? Not this room?"[l][r]
"I think this room is charming. No pantry or bunk beds, though."[l][r]
"Yeah, but..."[r]
"Right."[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
Yuri moved her face away from my ear.[l][r]
The sunlight reflecting in the room made her golden hair shine. The water droplets had already dried.[l][r]

"Let's go together. Our journey, Chi-chan and me."[l][r]
"Our... home, huh?"[l][r]

I looked straight into Yuri's eyes and said it.[l][r]
Yuri also looked straight into my eyes and said,[r]
it.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

